Package edu.uiowa.cs.warp

Class WarpGraph

java.lang.Object
edu.uiowa.cs.warp.WarpGraph
Direct Known Subclasses:
CommunicationGraphVisualization.CommunicationCostGraph, GraphVizVisualization.FlowDiGraph
public class WarpGraph extends Object
Builds a basic network graph and edge set that can be used for simulations and visualizations. The flows, nodes, and edges are defined in a WorkLoad object.
Version:
2.0 Fall 2025
Author:
sgoddard

    • getEdgeLabelForMap

      private String getEdgeLabelForMap(EdgeMap map, Edge edge, Boolean directed)
      Add a work load edge to the EdgeMap. If directed is true, the name key includes the flow, src, and snk nodes. If not, the name key is (node1, node2) where the src and snk are sorted lexicographically.
      Parameters:
      map - to which the edge is added
      edge - to be added to the map
      directed - indicates if the graph is directed or undirected

    • createEdgeMap

      Parameters:

      Returns:
      the map of edge names to edge objects
